casebody.data:
Wallace C. JONES Jr., Appellant(s)/Petitioner(s),
v.
The STATE of Florida, Appellee(s)/Respondent(s), CASE NO.: 3D18-1958 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. OCTOBER 3, 2018 LAGOA, FERNANDEZ and LUCK, JJ., concur.

Upon consideration, petitioner's motion to proceed in forma pauperis is granted, and petitioner may proceed in forma pauperis for purposes of this cause.

Following review of the petition for a writ of certiorari, it is ordered that said petition is hereby dismissed as a premature appeal pursuant to Florida Rule of Appellate Procedure 9.110(l).
